The Median of Medians algorithm is a deterministic algorithm that can find the kth smallest element in an unsorted list in O(n) time complexity. The median of a list is the kth smallest element where k = (n+1)/2 for odd n, and k = n/2 for even n.
Here is a Python code implementation of the Median of Medians algorithm to find the median of the set of integers represented in XML format:
